main event: Two airline pilots spotted a large, reddish-white object with green wings near Great Mills, Maryland on October 19, 1959.
interesting points: The object was 5-6 times larger than a star.
The object had green wings protruding from it.
The sighting lasted for approximately 25 minutes.
The weather conditions at the time were clear with 15 miles visibility.
sighted object: large, reddish-white object with green wings
witnesses: pilots of National Airlines Flight 118 and Eastern Airlines Flight 642
